<MudText Class="mb-8">This example is for uploading an image from file or from a camera of a cellphone.</MudText>

<br />
<MudText Typo="Typo.h5" GutterBottom="true">Brief description:</MudText>
<br />
<MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
    Entity "Images" contains Id, byte[] ImageData (which translates to VARBINARY(MAX) in MSSQL) and ImageName. <br />
    In ImageManipulation are located methods to check image orientation, scale it and convert to byte array as jpeg (for the lowest amount of space in DB).<br />
    Getting the image from device rely on <i>accept="image/*; capture=camera"</i>. Take any image or "capture" for devices with camera (cellphone..).<br />
</MudText>
